  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering, both at national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Key compliance measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk transactions\n\n4. Enforcement mechanisms:\n- Criminal penalties\n- Financial sanctions\n- Asset seizure\n- Regulatory fines\n- International cooperation in investigations\n\n5. Sectors covered:\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Professional services\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and investigative protocols.",
